Business Briefs
General Dynamics Corp.'s Land Systems division received a
$141.1 million contract modification to develop the Saudi
Arabian MIA-2 Abrams tank for desert warfare.
   ---
   Gillette Co. is expected to introduce shortly a women's
version of its popular Sensor razor, industry sources said.
   ---
   Discount Corp. of New York sold its fixed-income asset
management unit, Discount Corp. of New York Advisers, to
Patricia Blank de Klink, a founder of the unit. Terms weren't
disclosed.
   ---
   Aluminum Co. of America said it agreed to form a joint
venture with Hungarian Aluminium Industrial Corp. to make
aluminum sheet and extrusions in Szekesfehervar, Hungary.